MBS17690.description:
‐where a pre-anaesthesia consultation covered by an item in the range 17615–17625 is performed in-rooms if: 
a) the service is provided to a patient prior to an admitted patient episode of care involving anaesthesia; 
b) the service is not provided to an admitted patient of a hospital; 
c) the service is not provided on the day of admission to hospital for the subsequent episode of care involving anaesthesia services; 
and 
d) the service is of more than 15 mins in duration

CF790.description:
ANAESTHESIA for procedures within the peritoneal cavity in the upper abdomen, 
including any of the following: 
a) open cholecystectomy; 
b) gastrectomy; 
c) laparoscopically assisted nephrectomy; 
d) bowel shunts
